<Layout title="About David Jung — Jungdesign"><SectionIntro eyebrow="About / David Jung" title="A designed life, still in motion"/><section class="about-layout"><div class="about-image"><img src="/images/artworks/Self1.jpg" alt="Self portrait by David Jung"/><span>SELF / OBSERVATION / REFLECTION</span></div><div class="about-copy"><p class="big-copy">David Jung has practised for about 60 years as a professional designer and project manager.</p><p>Across that working life, he learned to notice how form meets use, how structure carries an idea, and how a project becomes real through patient attention. In retirement, painting has become his main creative practice.</p><p>The paintings are not a departure from design so much as its continuation by other means. They carry a lifetime of looking at colour, material, people, objects and systems—then give that discipline room for humour, memory and possibility.</p><p>Jungdesign now describes both the history and the ongoing experiment: careful work, made with curiosity.</p><a class="button" href="/paintings">See the work</a></div></section><section class="values"><div><b>01</b><h2>Notice</h2><p>The telling edge, gesture, reflection or odd little object.</p></div><div><b>02</b><h2>Compose</h2><p>Give every element a reason to be in the frame.</p></div><div><b>03</b><h2>Play</h2><p>Let precision make room for surprise.</p></div></section><ContactCTA/></Layout>
